    <p>{`Vector can be installed through the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://nixos.org/nix/"
      }}>{`Nix package manager`}</a>{` via
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/blob/master/pkgs/tools/misc/vector/default.nix"
      }}>{`Vector's Nix package`}</a>{`. This package manager is
generally used on `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://nixos.org/"
      }}>{`NixOS`}</a>{`.`}</p>
    <Alert type="warning" mdxType="Alert">
      <p>{`Because Vector must be manually updated on Nix, new Vector releases will be
delayed. Generally new Vector releases are made available within a few days.`}</p>
    </Alert>
    {
      /*
          THIS FILE IS AUTOGENERATED!
           To make changes please edit the template located at:
           website/docs/setup/installation/package-managers/nix.md.erb
      */
    }
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "install"
    }}>{`Install`}</h2>
    <Tabs block={true} defaultValue="daemon" values={[{
      "label": "As a Daemon",
      "value": "daemon"
    }]} mdxType="Tabs">
      <TabItem value="daemon" mdxType="TabItem">
        <p>{`The `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "/docs/setup/deployment/strategies/#daemon"
          }}>{`daemon deployment strategy`}</a>{` is designed for data
collection on a single host. Vector runs in the background, in its own process,
collecting `}<em parentName="p">{`all`}</em>{` data for that host.
Typically data is collected from a process manager, such as Journald via
Vector's `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "/docs/reference/sources/journald/"
          }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`journald`}</inlineCode>{` source`}</a>{`, but can be collected
through any of Vector's `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "/docs/reference/sources/"
          }}>{`sources`}</a>{`.
The following diagram demonstrates how it works.`}</p>
        <DaemonDiagram platformName={null} sourceName={null} sinkName={null} mdxType="DaemonDiagram" />
        <hr></hr>
        <Tabs centered={true} className={"rounded"} defaultValue={"nix"} placeholder="Please choose an installation method..." select={false} size={null} values={[{
          "group": "Package managers",
          "label": "Nix",
          "value": "nix"
        }]} mdxType="Tabs">
          <TabItem value="nix" mdxType="TabItem">
            <Steps headingDepth={3} mdxType="Steps">
              <ol>
                <li parentName="ol">
                  <h3 parentName="li" {...{
                    "id": "install-vector"
                  }}>{`Install Vector`}</h3>
                  <pre parentName="li"><code parentName="pre" {...{
                      "className": "language-bash"
                    }}>{`nix-env --file https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/archive/master.tar.gz --install --attr vector
`}</code></pre>
                  <CodeExplanation mdxType="CodeExplanation">
                    <ul parentName="li">
                      <li parentName="ul">{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`--file`}</inlineCode>{` flag ensures that you're installing the latest stable version
of Vector (0.9.2).`}</li>
                      <li parentName="ul">{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`--attr`}</inlineCode>{` improves installation speed.`}</li>
                    </ul>
                  </CodeExplanation>
                  <p parentName="li"><a parentName="p" {...{
                      "href": "/docs/setup/installation/package-managers/nix/#versions"
                    }}>{`Looking for a specific version?`}</a></p>
                </li>
                <li parentName="ol">
                  <h3 parentName="li" {...{
                    "id": "configure-vector"
                  }}>{`Configure Vector`}</h3>
                  <ConfigExample format="toml" path={"/etc/vector/vector.toml"} sourceName={"journald"} sinkName={null} mdxType="ConfigExample" />
                </li>
                <li parentName="ol">
                  <h3 parentName="li" {...{
                    "id": "start-vector"
                  }}>{`Start Vector`}</h3>
                  <pre parentName="li"><code parentName="pre" {...{
                      "className": "language-bash"
                    }}>{`vector --config /etc/vector/vector.toml
`}</code></pre>
                  <CodeExplanation mdxType="CodeExplanation">
                    <ul parentName="li">
                      <li parentName="ul"><inlineCode parentName="li">{`vector`}</inlineCode>{` is placed in your `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`$PATH`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</li>
                      <li parentName="ul">{`You must create a `}<a parentName="li" {...{
                          "href": "/docs/setup/configuration/"
                        }}>{`Vector configuration file`}</a>{` to
successfully start Vector.`}</li>
                    </ul>
                  </CodeExplanation>
                </li>
              </ol>
            </Steps>
          </TabItem>
        </Tabs>
      </TabItem>
    </Tabs>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "configuring"
    }}>{`Configuring`}</h2>
    <p>{`The `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/blob/master/pkgs/tools/misc/vector/default.nix"
      }}>{`Vector nix package`}</a>{` does not install any
configuration files by default. You'll need to create a
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/setup/configuration/"
      }}>{`Vector configuration file`}</a>{` and pass it to Vector via the
`}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`--config`}</inlineCode>{` flag when `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/administration/process-management/#starting"
      }}>{`starting`}</a>{` Vector.`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "deploying"
    }}>{`Deploying`}</h2>
    <p>{`How you deploy Vector is largely dependent on your use case and environment.
Please see the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/setup/deployment/"
      }}>{`deployment section`}</a>{` for more info on how to
deploy Vector.`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "administering"
    }}>{`Administering`}</h2>
    <p>{`The Vector nix package does not use Systemd by default, but Vector does provide
a `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://github.com/timberio/vector/blob/master/distribution/systemd/vector.service"
      }}>{`Systemd service file`}</a>{` that you can use as a
starting point. How you manage the Vector process is up to you, and the
process administration section covers how to do this:`}</p>
    <Jump to="/docs/administration/" mdxType="Jump">Administration</Jump>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "uninstalling"
    }}>{`Uninstalling`}</h2>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`nix-env --uninstall vector
`}</code></pre>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "updating"
    }}>{`Updating`}</h2>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`nix-env --file https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/archive/master.tar.gz --upgrade vector
`}</code></pre>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "package"
    }}>{`Package`}</h2>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "architectures"
    }}>{`Architectures`}</h3>
    <p>{`Vector's Nix packages only support the X86_64 architecture.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "versions"
    }}>{`Versions`}</h3>
    <p>{`Installing previous versions of Vector through `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`nix`}</inlineCode>{` is possible, but not
straightforward. For example, installing Vector `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`0.7.1`}</inlineCode>{` can be achieved with
the following command:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`nix-env --file https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/archive/20bbe6cba68fb9d37b5d0e373b6180dce2961e0d.tar.gz --install --attr vector
`}</code></pre>
    <p><inlineCode parentName="p">{`20bbe6...`}</inlineCode>{` represents the commit sha for the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`0.7.1`}</inlineCode>{` on the
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/blob/master/pkgs/tools/misc/vector/default.nix"
      }}>{`nix package repo`}</a>{`.`}</p>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "listing-versions--commit-shas"
    }}>{`Listing Versions & Commit SHAs`}</h4>
    <p>{`For situations that required automated retrieval, we've thrown thogether this
handy Ruby function that will list the Vector versions and their commit sha:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-ruby"
      }}>{`require "net/http"
require "json"

# Returns a hash mapping Vector versions to commits in \`nixpkgs/nixos\` repository
def nix_versions
  nixpkgs_repo = "nixos/nixpkgs"
  commits_url = "https://api.github.com/repos/#{nixpkgs_repo}/commits?path=pkgs/tools/misc/vector"

  response = Net::HTTP.get URI(commits_url)
  items = JSON.parse response

  versions = {}
  for item in items do
    match = item["commit"]["message"].match "^vector:.*(\\\\d+\\.\\\\d+\\.\\\\d+)$"
    if match
      version = match[1]
      versions[version] = item["sha"]
    end
  end

  versions
end
`}</code></pre>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "source-files"
    }}>{`Source Files`}</h3>
    <p>{`Vector's Nix source files are located in the
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/blob/master/pkgs/tools/misc/vector/default.nix"
      }}>{`Nix repo`}</a>{`.`}</p>
